    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Acinodendron macrostachyum are fever, which has been traditionally used to treat by boiling the roots in water; wounds, as the plant has been used in traditional medicine to apply a paste made from its roots to accelerate healing; and gastritis, with its leaves used to prepare a tea that has been shown to reduce inflammation in the stomach lining. The roots of Acinodendron macrostachyum have also been used to treat rheumatism, by applying a decoction made from them to the affected area. Additionally, its leaves have been used to treat diarrhea, by preparing a tea that has been shown to reduce the frequency and severity of episodes. Acinodendron macrostachyum has also been used to treat skin conditions such as eczema, with its leaves used to prepare a paste that has been shown to reduce inflammation and itching. Furthermore, its roots have been used to treat respiratory issues such as bronchitis, with a decoction made from them shown to reduce coughing and difficulty breathing.",
