    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Acinodendron macrostachyum are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, antimicrobial, antifungal, and analgesic. The plant's antioxidant property helps to protect cells from oxidative damage, thereby preventing chronic diseases such as cancer and cardiovascular diseases. The anti-inflammatory property of Acinodendron macrostachyum reduces inflammation and pain, making it effective in treating conditions like arthritis. The analgesic property of this plant is attributed to the presence of bioactive compounds such as flavonoids, which have been shown to exhibit pain-relieving activity. The plant's antimicrobial and antifungal properties are due to the presence of saponins and volatile oils, which have been found to exhibit antimicrobial and antifungal activities against various pathogens.",
