    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Acinodendron macrostachyum are flavonoids, such as quercetin and kaempferol, and triterpenoids, including ursolic acid and oleanolic acid. These compounds have been found to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, which contribute to their healing effects. The flavonoids have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines, while the triterpenoids have been found to scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The combination of these compounds in Acinodendron macrostachyum is thought to be responsible for its traditional use in treating various health conditions, including fever, pain, and inflammation. Studies have demonstrated the potential of Acinodendron macrostachyum extracts to exhibit therapeutic benefits in the treatment of oxidative stress-related diseases.",
