    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Acinodendron macrostachyum are tea, infusion, tincture, decoction, and salve. Tea and infusion are prepared from the leaves by steeping them in hot water to create a liquid extract rich in flavonoids and phenolic compounds, which have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. The leaves can also be made into a decoction by boiling them in water for an extended period to release their bioactive compounds, such as glycosides and saponins. A tincture is prepared by soaking the leaves in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin to create a concentrated liquid extract, which can be used to treat various health conditions. A salve is prepared by infusing the leaves in a carrier oil like coconut or olive oil to create a topical cream or ointment that can be applied directly to the skin to treat wounds, inflammation, and other skin issues.",
